Final Project Checklist
Project Name: Django Web Service
Deployment Status: Successfully deployed to Render
Deployment URL: https://final-project-qd1k.onrender.com
Summary of the needed items
The project meets all Baseline requirements, exceeds the minimum requirements for good, better, and best tiers.
 Baseline (All Implemented)
Requirement	Status	Implementation Notes
Web request/response lifecycle	✔️	Django handles this by default.
DNS → IP → HTTP (context)	✔️	Covered by deployment and Django’s request handling.
HTTP methods & headers	✔️	POST/GET in forms and views.
WSGI (where HTTP meets Python)	✔️	Django uses WSGI.
Django’s job: URLs + views	✔️	urls.py and views.py are configured.
Getting Django set up (venv, startproject)	✔️	Project is set up.
URLconf basics: path()/urlpatterns	✔️	Used in urls.py.
Route converters (<int:>, <slug:>)	✔️	Used for post slugs.
Ordering/specificity of patterns	✔️	Patterns are ordered.
Function-Based Views (FBV)	✔️	Used for registration/profile.
HttpRequest/HttpResponse essentials	✔️	Used in views.
TEMPLATES settings & loaders	✔️	Configured in settings.py.
Rendering from views (render, CBV context)	✔️	Used in views.
Form classes: fields → HTML	✔️	ModelForm and UserRegisterForm.
GET vs POST, bound forms, is_valid()	✔️	Used in registration and post forms.
CSRF & {% csrf_token %}	✔️	All POST forms include {% csrf_token %}.
Define models and fields	✔️	Post model defined.
Migrations (makemigrations/migrate)	✔️	Used.
Enable admin and register models	✔️	admin.py configured.
App config and structure	✔️	Standard Django app structure.
Login/logout flow	✔️	Django auth URLs implemented.
What middleware is and order	✔️	Standard middleware configured.
STATIC_URL and finders	✔️	Configured in settings.py.
Django TestCase basics	✔️	tests.py includes basic tests.
Env vars and secret settings	✔️	Used in settings.py.
DEBUG=False, ALLOWED_HOSTS hygiene	✔️	Controlled by environment variables.
MEDIA_URL/ROOT and uploads	✔️	Configured in settings.py.
Use request.session safely	✔️	Django sessions enabled.
Settings and configuration	✔️	Configured in settings.py.
Use built-in manage.py commands	✔️	Used for migration, runserver.
Paginate heavy lists	✔️	PostListView paginates posts.
CSRF, XSS, and input sanitizing	✔️	CSRF and Django’s built-in protections.
Logging and error pages	✔️	Logging middleware and error handling implemented.

